                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(Thank you Lady Jewel ... I'll see what I can do)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Guide Kledoki said, "We have arrived. This is where you will find the Wizard spell merchants."
<br />

<br />
Koori made a mental note to sit down and study the map of Gukta someday soon.
<br />

<br />
She approached the Scribe and bowed.  "Hail, Master Scribe Uklo!"</span>
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/jeremy_moffitt/images/everquest/uklo.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Master Scribe Uklo frowned "Please hurry and finish that which I have asked of you. His spirit is in torment and must be put to rest."
<br />

<br />
The enchantress chuckled and pulled the broken pieces of the sword from her pouch.  "Patience old one, here are the items you requested from me."  She laid out the items into the eager hands of the other.
<br />

<br />
Master Scribe Uklo says "I just can't believe that I am holding all three items. You are truly amazing. Now let me see . . . Seems the blade has been fused with some sort of material. We must remove this before the sword can be restored. I think this calls for an old recipe. Take this distiller and use it to mix some skyash bile and a pinch of drake lava powder together. You should be able to find the bile in the mountains of fire and the drake lava powder is best retrieved from fire drakes in the mountains of lava. Bring me the result and I should be able to restore this ancient weapon."
<br />

<br />
Koori frowned; she had taken off this morning on her own ... the items the old frog requested would have been easier with Meredith at her side.  "Ah well, might as well see this through."  As she walked toward the exit of the outpost she asked for aid though the bonds of the guild.  Palidoc the Templar from last eve and Adjantis the holy sword wielding Knight quickly agreed to meet her in the Planes of Knowledge.
<br />

<br />
Basher Nuglar rustled around in his cage as she passed, and let out a sigh. "Mes wan' outta herez!!"
<br />

<br />
~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~*~'
<br />

<br />
The collection of Skyash Bile took only a moment in the heated rocks of Skyfire and took even less time to secure the Drake Lava Powder from a tiny drake in Lavastorm Mountains ... it took more time to walk between the different lands then it did to find the items.  
<br />

<br />
Koori placed both the bile and powder into the small distiller Uklo had given her.  It combined into some kind of red goo ... she placed it inside an empty vial as the other two watched her.
<br />

<br />
"So what's next?" Palidoc asked as he took a drink of Elven Wine.
<br />

<br />
"You drink like a dwarf..." Koori murmured under her breath.  "Why don't the two of you head back to the Plane of Knowledge?  I'll gate and go see if my quest has been completed."
<br />

<br />
The other two gave her mock salutes as they began their jog back once more to the Plane of Knowledge.  Koori's path took her once more to the side of the Scribe Uklo.  The frog grinned as she handed him the vial she had created.  "Words cannot describe what you have done. This is truly a wonderful day for our citizens. Now I can rebuild the sword and our hero can finally finish that which he started. Please, while this is more then enough proof of your loyalty, I must ask that you take this sword and place it in the remains. Return with proof that it has been done and I shall reward you with the knowledge you seek."
<br />

<br />
Master Scribe Uklo said, "Please hurry and finish that which I have asked of you. His spirit is in torment and must be put to rest."
<br />

<br />
"So ... are we done?"  Adjantis asked from afar.
<br />

<br />
"Not yet, guild kin ... can you meet me at the valley to Rathe Mountains?  I guess there is an old skeleton to see and I feel uneasy about it."  Koori slipped the heavy sword the frog had given her into a magical bag, lessening the load.
<br />

<br />
"On our way!"
<br />

<br />
"Race you there!"
<br />

<br />
Koori chose to run through the swamplands and arrived well after the others ... Adjantis was finishing a Fish Roll while Palidoc was once again sipping at a bottle of Elven Wine.  "Sorry to keep you waiting ... are we ready?"
<br />

<br />
"Aye, lead on!"
<br />

<br />
Without Meredith to guide her it took a couple of tries to find the correct ruins ... but once she had, it was easy to find the old froglok's remains.  "I think we should take a moment to prepare ourselves, I believe there is a battle to be done."
<br />

<br />
"With undead?" Adjantis asked with a hopeful grin.
<br />

<br />
"Aye, you undead stalker ... this will be the end to an ancient battle."
<br />

<br />
Taking out a peridot from her pouch she cast it in the air, a magical armor surrounded the paladin, she did the same to the cleric.  "Just in case ... oh and if things turn nasty ... my apologies before hand."
<br />

<br />
Adjantis chuckled and tightened his grip on his weapon.  "Let's do this."
<br />

<br />
Koori bent down and placed the sword deemed Marr's Retribution into the skeleton hand of the other.  There was a shimmer of magic and a spectral figure appeared emanating a powerful yet ghastly aura. Warrior Spirit Chalex said, "Your kindness has given me a chance to finish that which I started. While I thank thee for restoring my blade and bringing it to me I am not worthy to wield it until I have destroyed the one who killed me. Please hold my sword until I have redeemed myself by vanquishing the vile Troll Captain Krignok. Now I must ask that you protect me, I can feel his presence close by and once again he is not alone."
<br />

<br />
Koori took back the sword from the undead frog that had appeared.  In his hand he had the flaming sword of a paladin.
<br />

<br />
Warrior Spirit Chalex shouted, "Come forth coward, this time we fight on equal terms!"
<br />

<br />
The ground beneath the trio began to shake and from the dirt undead minions appeared ... littering the ground with rotting flesh.
<br />

<br />
Koori heard Palidoc whisper a prayer to his God but then lost sight of both of her companions in the horde of the undead.  Their hands clawed at her, but the magical barrier she had placed on protected her.
<br />

<br />
Warrior Spirit Chalex shouted 'Have at thee Krignok, today I shall find my peace!'
<br />

<br />
From the chaos Koori heard Adjantis's death cry ... over-powered by the swarm of undead.
<br />

<br />
Undead Captain Krignok shouted "Your beliefs will find you dead by my hands once again frog!"
<br />

<br />
Warrior Spirit Chalex shouts "Give it up Krignok, you are outmatched when facing a paladin of Mithaniel Marr!"
<br />

<br />
Undead Captain Krignok shouts, "Do not think that you will win. You could not finish me then and you will not be able to do it now!"
<br />

<br />
Warrior Spirit Chalex shouts, "You shall feel my vengeance on this day dirty troll!"
<br />

<br />
Koori stumbled under the power of her attackers ... beneath her was the body of the brave cleric.  "I'm sorry Chalex, you will have to fight this battle on your own ... we are not strong enough to aid you."
<br />

<br />
Undead Captain Krignok shouted, "I do not need my legions to finish you!"
<br />

<br />
Warrior Spirit Chalex shouted, "Through the strength of Mithaniel I shall be redeemed with your destruction!"
<br />

<br />
Troll Captain Krignok said, "I yield Chalex, you are truly a worthy opponent."
<br />

<br />
Images of the dead whipped around the air as Krignok returned to the spectral world taking his remaining minions with him. Koori glanced around, the bodies of her friends ... her own robe soaked in blood ... her wounds near fatal ... then her eyes moved over to the warrior spirit. He thanked Mithaniel for a second chance ... as he stood before her redeemed. Their eyes meet and he asked for the sword Koori still held.  As Chalex took the sword he began to change. Old becomes new right before her eyes as the touch of Mithaniel reshaped the warrior spirit. "Thank you again Koori. Your kindness has allowed my spirit to go home.. Please show this to my people so they will have a memory of what you have done."  Waving goodbye Chalex The Redeemed disappeared just as quickly as he appeared.</span>
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/jeremy_moffitt/images/everquest/redeemed.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: normal">Koori looked down at the locket in her hand, the two men reassured her all was well and they would be back soon to collect their belongings.  The enchantress cast rune upon herself once more in case any wandering creatures thought of her to be quick prey because of her wounds and rested.  The two men did return quickly and after making sure she had been healed, sent her on her way ... while they recouped enough for the run back.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Guide Kledoki said, "We have arrived. This is where you will find the Wizard spell merchants."
<br />

<br />
Uklo knelt before her as tears of happiness rolled down his face. "I thank you Koori. Since our creation it has been rare that we have received such kindness. You will always be welcome in our city and future generations will croak the story of your greatness. Please take this as a small token of my gratitude you have truly earned it."
<br />

<br />
Koori took the offered scroll but watched as Master Scribe Uklo opened the spectral locket, eager to see what is inside. Suddenly an all too familiar image appeared next him.
<br />

<br />
The memory of Chalex said, "Thank you again adventurer. Thank you for helping me get back that which I lost."
<br />

<br />
Koori smiled as the Scribe and Paladin stood together once more ... she felt good in what she had done, and the scroll in her hand no longer seemed as important.  She had heard travelers of old speak of the magic being gone from the lands ... but sometimes you just needed to look a little harder.  
<br />

<br />
"Today has been a good day ... Farewell Brave Ones." She said bowing.
<br />

<br />
Chalex looked toward her and smiled before fading away, a memory once more.</span>
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.geocities.com/jeremy_moffitt/images/everquest/memory.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
